    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a great start for the lesson. To make sure the kids get the full picture, could you also explain how this differs from 'procedural due process'? I want them to understand the distinction between the two.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Procedural due process is simply about *how* the government acts, demanding fair processes like proper notice and a chance to be heard before someone is deprived of life, liberty, or property. Substantive due process, however, is about *what* the government is allowed to do in the first place, protecting fundamental rights regardless of how fairly the process was followed. One focuses on the fairness of the game, while the other focuses on whether the rules themselves are fundamentally just.",
      "source": "target",
