    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. Some critics and legal scholars argue that the idea of 'substantive due process' is actually pretty problematic because it allows judges to essentially create new rights that aren't explicitly written in the Constitution. They say it's a way of bypassing the democratic process. How would you address that criticism in my lesson plan?",
