      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "This criticism is a common, yet deeply rooted, argument from those who fear judicial activism, which is a valid concern when discussing the limits of judicial power. The counterargument is that the Constitution is not merely a list of procedures; it is a living document designed to protect inherent human dignity against the tyranny of the majority. When the legislature fails to protect fundamental liberties, the judiciary must step in to uphold the foundational promise of the American system.",
      "source": "target",
